cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.DB 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category as it deals with detecting and characterizing Sybil accounts in an online social network. It could also belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category as Sybil attacks are a security threat. The paper also analyzes the link creation behavior of Sybil accounts, which could fall under the cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) category. Additionally, since the paper involves data analysis and measurement, it could belong to the cs.DB (Databases) category. Finally, since the paper deals with online communities and file-sharing systems, it could also belong to the cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) category.
